    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-29T02:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-29T02:35:00-05:00" n="615"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d615">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Amiranian/61: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-29T11:00:00+03:25"
                            >May 29, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. My 49, May 21, 3 p.m. I am informed Hart who is now in Kabul has decided to
                    postpone notification to the Afghan Government until June 4 and formal written
                    notification here until June 6. I also hear that Clapp intends to apply for oil
                    concession in southeastern Iran. It is difficult to reconcile these maneuvers
                    with the <pb facs="0763" n="755" xml:id="pg_755"/> company’s decision and they
                    may have a deplorable effect upon a situation which is already bad enough.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
